I mean he was making
a lot of enemies.

00:34:34.179 --> 00:34:37.480 align:middle line:84%
And everybody knew that John
Kennedy had a lot of women

00:34:37.480 --> 00:34:39.940 align:middle line:84%
in his life, including
famous ones like Marilyn

00:34:39.940 --> 00:34:43.940 align:middle line:84%
Monroe and Angie Dickinson,
but it was OK in those days.

00:34:43.940 --> 00:34:45.730 align:middle line:84%
You couldn't take
them out with that.

00:34:45.730 --> 00:34:47.710 align:middle line:10%
They had to take him
out with a bullet.

00:34:47.710 --> 00:34:49.929 align:middle line:10%
And, of course, his
brother came along and--

00:34:49.929 --> 00:34:53.115 align:middle line:10%
>>REGINA: But when you say that,
the media was more discreet.

00:34:53.115 --> 00:34:57.280 align:middle line:84%
They didn't necessarily-- that
wasn't the evening news with, I

00:34:57.280 --> 00:35:01.520 align:middle line:84%
think, you had Walter Cronkite
in those days and Chet Huntley.

00:35:01.520 --> 00:35:04.110 align:middle line:90%
That wasn't the evening news.

00:35:04.110 --> 00:35:05.742 align:middle line:90%
Now that would be headline news.

00:35:05.742 --> 00:35:06.450 align:middle line:90%
>>PERKINS: Right.

00:35:06.450 --> 00:35:10.020 align:middle line:84%
We've deteriorated so much,
because in those days,

00:35:10.020 --> 00:35:12.830 align:middle line:84%
like still in so
much of the world,

00:35:12.830 --> 00:35:14.970 align:middle line:84%
a politician or
leader's personal life

00:35:14.970 --> 00:35:17.330 align:middle line:84%
is considered just
that, personal life.

00:35:17.330 --> 00:35:22.200 align:middle line:84%
And we all have weaknesses,
and who can be perfect?

00:35:22.200 --> 00:35:25.440 align:middle line:84%
But today, we have a
totally different standard

00:35:25.440 --> 00:35:29.350 align:middle line:84%
and that gives a lot more
control to the press.

00:35:29.350 --> 00:35:31.610 align:middle line:84%
And let's face it,
the mainstream media

00:35:31.610 --> 00:35:33.680 align:middle line:84%
is owned by the
corporatocracy, either

00:35:33.680 --> 00:35:35.580 align:middle line:84%
through outright
ownership or it's

00:35:35.580 --> 00:35:37.206 align:middle line:84%
controlled through
advertising budgets.

00:35:37.206 --> 00:35:39.746 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: Well, and they have
a lot of CIA operatives at high

00:35:39.746 --> 00:35:40.246 align:middle line:90%
places--

00:35:40.246 --> 00:35:41.121 align:middle line:90%
>>PERKINS: Of course.

00:35:41.121 --> 00:35:42.440 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: -with network media.

00:35:42.440 --> 00:35:43.505 align:middle line:84%
>>PERKINS: There's a
tremendous interchange

00:35:43.505 --> 00:35:44.796 align:middle line:90%
of information between the two.

00:35:44.796 --> 00:35:46.092 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Yes there is.

00:35:46.092 --> 00:35:48.940 align:middle line:84%
Well, and they said in
editorial positions as well.

00:35:48.940 --> 00:35:50.530 align:middle line:90%
People need to know that.

00:35:50.530 --> 00:35:51.940 align:middle line:90%
>>PERKINS: It's absolutely true.

00:35:51.940 --> 00:35:56.350 align:middle line:84%
There's a revolving door where
they're constantly changing.

00:35:56.350 --> 00:35:58.616 align:middle line:84%
And the same with
Robert Kennedy.

00:35:58.616 --> 00:35:59.740 align:middle line:90%
And Martin Luther King, Jr.

00:35:59.740 --> 00:36:01.570 align:middle line:84%
People knew that
Martin Luther King, Jr,

00:36:01.570 --> 00:36:04.460 align:middle line:84%
had what we might call
a shady background.

00:36:04.460 --> 00:36:05.990 align:middle line:90%
He had skeletons in his closet.

00:36:05.990 --> 00:36:07.630 align:middle line:90%
But they didn't come out.

00:36:07.630 --> 00:36:09.600 align:middle line:84%
Partly because the media
didn't bring it out.

00:36:09.600 --> 00:36:12.500 align:middle line:84%
The media was much more
independent in those days,

00:36:12.500 --> 00:36:14.090 align:middle line:84%
and there was a
different standard.

00:36:14.090 --> 00:36:17.190 align:middle line:84%
But also partly because
people didn't-- it wasn't that

00:36:17.190 --> 00:36:18.500 align:middle line:90%
important.

00:36:18.500 --> 00:36:21.150 align:middle line:90%
And things all changed.

00:36:21.150 --> 00:36:23.450 align:middle line:84%
And I think the women's
movement had a lot to do this.

00:36:23.450 --> 00:36:24.310 align:middle line:90%
I'm all for it.

00:36:24.310 --> 00:36:26.560 align:middle line:84%
I'm totally for what came
out of the women's movement.

00:36:26.560 --> 00:36:29.310 align:middle line:84%
But it did create a
different moral standard.

00:36:29.310 --> 00:36:33.800 align:middle line:84%
So when Clinton comes
along, one of the big voices

00:36:33.800 --> 00:36:36.910 align:middle line:84%
was against Monica Lewinsky
expressed by a lot of women

00:36:36.910 --> 00:36:40.580 align:middle line:84%
around the country
because of poor Hillary.

00:36:40.580 --> 00:36:42.620 align:middle line:84%
And there's a whole
different standard.

00:36:42.620 --> 00:36:45.540 align:middle line:84%
And in any case,
whatever it meant,

00:36:45.540 --> 00:36:48.850 align:middle line:84%
it meant that a president
could be impeached because

00:36:48.850 --> 00:36:52.565 align:middle line:84%
of a sexual act, which wasn't
even that interesting if you

00:36:52.565 --> 00:36:53.075 align:middle line:90%
ask me.

00:36:53.075 --> 00:36:53.675 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: No.

00:36:53.675 --> 00:36:56.050 align:middle line:84%
>>PERKINS: Most of the world
laughed at this whole thing.

00:36:56.050 --> 00:36:57.890 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: I know,
especially the French.

00:36:57.890 --> 00:36:59.380 align:middle line:84%
It was like, come
on, get a clue.

00:36:59.380 --> 00:37:02.030 align:middle line:84%
These are world leaders, they've
always done this, always will.

00:37:02.030 --> 00:37:04.571 align:middle line:10%
>>PERKINS: And soon after that
we stopped eating French fries

00:37:04.571 --> 00:37:07.686 align:middle line:10%
and ate Freedom Fries.

00:37:07.686 --> 00:37:09.920 align:middle line:10%
That's one way to get back
at those immoral French.

00:37:09.920 --> 00:37:12.520 align:middle line:10%
>>REGINA: That didn't take.

00:37:12.520 --> 00:37:16.560 align:middle line:84%
McDonald's still
sells French fries.

00:37:16.560 --> 00:37:18.560 align:middle line:84%
>>PERKINS: But in any
case, a new standard's set

00:37:18.560 --> 00:37:23.570 align:middle line:84%
and there's no doubt in my mind
that Linda Tripp was an agent.

00:37:23.570 --> 00:37:26.435 align:middle line:84%
And she'd been in the
Bush administration,

00:37:26.435 --> 00:37:31.300 align:middle line:84%
and she'd been in the Pentagon,
and she set Monica up.

00:37:31.300 --> 00:37:34.160 align:middle line:84%
She gave her a microphone and
said, don't wash the dress,

00:37:34.160 --> 00:37:35.610 align:middle line:90%
don't launder it.

00:37:35.610 --> 00:37:38.570 align:middle line:90%
It was a set up, it was a hit.

00:37:38.570 --> 00:37:40.150 align:middle line:90%
And Clinton got taken out.

00:37:40.150 --> 00:37:42.870 align:middle line:84%
And it looked as though at
that time that Clinton was--

00:37:42.870 --> 00:37:45.840 align:middle line:84%
as he was getting prepared when
he left office to maybe go up

00:37:45.840 --> 00:37:48.750 align:middle line:84%
against the Federal Reserve,
maybe do a few other things.

00:37:48.750 --> 00:37:50.430 align:middle line:84%
But he hasn't done
anything, obviously,

00:37:50.430 --> 00:37:52.122 align:middle line:84%
except now he hangs
out with the Bushes.

00:37:52.122 --> 00:37:52.830 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: I know.

00:37:52.830 --> 00:37:53.500 align:middle line:84%
I was just going
to bring that up.

00:37:53.500 --> 00:37:54.529 align:middle line:90%
Now they're all friends.

00:37:54.529 --> 00:37:55.820 align:middle line:90%
>>PERKINS: They're all friends.

00:37:55.820 --> 00:37:57.650 align:middle line:90%
Well, he got the message.

00:37:57.650 --> 00:38:03.910 align:middle line:84%
And I'm sure that Obama, if
he hadn't happened before,

00:38:03.910 --> 00:38:05.700 align:middle line:84%
as soon as he walked
into the Oval Office,

00:38:05.700 --> 00:38:06.900 align:middle line:90%
he got the message.

00:38:06.900 --> 00:38:09.600 align:middle line:84%
Like you're very, very
vulnerable, Mr. Obama,

00:38:09.600 --> 00:38:11.780 align:middle line:84%
and you've got to
realize that you've

00:38:11.780 --> 00:38:13.480 align:middle line:84%
got a few skeletons
in your closet.

00:38:13.480 --> 00:38:17.810 align:middle line:84%
And even if you don't,
between the FBI and the media,

00:38:17.810 --> 00:38:22.040 align:middle line:84%
we can create them, so
you better play the game.

00:38:22.040 --> 00:38:25.020 align:middle line:84%
And then they shot a few shots
across his bow, you know,

00:38:25.020 --> 00:38:27.305 align:middle line:84%
like is he a citizen,
is he gay, whatever

00:38:27.305 --> 00:38:28.430 align:middle line:90%
all these different things.

00:38:28.430 --> 00:38:29.585 align:middle line:90%
Was he born in Indonesia?

00:38:29.585 --> 00:38:30.680 align:middle line:90%
I don't know.

00:38:30.680 --> 00:38:37.240 align:middle line:84%
And not too long after that, the
head of the IMF, Strauss Kahn,

00:38:37.240 --> 00:38:39.570 align:middle line:84%
was brought down
by an accusation

00:38:39.570 --> 00:38:43.770 align:middle line:84%
by a chambermaid in
a hotel in New York.

00:38:43.770 --> 00:38:46.816 align:middle line:84%
And which was subsequently
thrown out of the courts.

00:38:46.816 --> 00:38:48.190 align:middle line:84%
I don't know the
truth behind it.

00:38:48.190 --> 00:38:49.400 align:middle line:84%
Maybe he raped her,
maybe he didn't.

00:38:49.400 --> 00:38:50.070 align:middle line:90%
I have no idea.

00:38:50.070 --> 00:38:53.690 align:middle line:84%
But what I do know is that when
something like that happens,

00:38:53.690 --> 00:38:58.300 align:middle line:84%
it puts the fear of God in Obama
and every other politician.

00:38:58.300 --> 00:39:01.230 align:middle line:84%
Because what they see is it
doesn't matter whether it turns

00:39:01.230 --> 00:39:03.880 align:middle line:84%
out to be true or not,
all you've got to do

00:39:03.880 --> 00:39:08.090 align:middle line:84%
is have a scandal, a rumor,
and you're emasculated.

00:39:08.090 --> 00:39:09.410 align:middle line:90%
You're assassinated.

00:39:09.410 --> 00:39:12.400 align:middle line:84%
Character assassination
is every bit as effective

00:39:12.400 --> 00:39:15.870 align:middle line:84%
as physical assassination
in terms of politics.

00:39:15.870 --> 00:39:21.320 align:middle line:84%
And the way that the CIA works
with corporations to help them

00:39:21.320 --> 00:39:24.700 align:middle line:84%
around the world establish
themselves, and it's mutual.

00:39:24.700 --> 00:39:27.350 align:middle line:84%
They work with each other
very, very, very closely.

00:39:27.350 --> 00:39:29.640 align:middle line:90%
It's a complex system.

00:39:29.640 --> 00:39:33.743 align:middle line:84%
And I wish I could say there's
this conspiracy with one person

00:39:33.743 --> 00:39:34.570 align:middle line:90%
up there.

00:39:34.570 --> 00:39:37.880 align:middle line:84%
Because if we believe that and
we could find that one person,

00:39:37.880 --> 00:39:39.440 align:middle line:84%
we could take care
of everything.

00:39:39.440 --> 00:39:40.040 align:middle line:90%
But it isn't.

00:39:40.040 --> 00:39:41.560 align:middle line:84%
It's much more
complex than that.

00:39:41.560 --> 00:39:44.560 align:middle line:84%
I think it's really
important for we, the people,

00:39:44.560 --> 00:39:47.390 align:middle line:84%
in the United States and around
the world to understand this.

00:39:47.390 --> 00:39:49.050 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: Meanwhile,
we have Greece

00:39:49.050 --> 00:39:50.190 align:middle line:90%
and what's happened there.

00:39:50.190 --> 00:39:52.760 align:middle line:84%
And you just wrote a
recent article on that.

00:39:52.760 --> 00:39:54.330 align:middle line:84%
What is your perception
when you look

00:39:54.330 --> 00:39:57.500 align:middle line:84%
at it from an economic
hitman point of view,

00:39:57.500 --> 00:39:59.580 align:middle line:84%
you look at it from
a debt point of view,

00:39:59.580 --> 00:40:02.870 align:middle line:84%
and then also the repercussions,
which, as you say,

00:40:02.870 --> 00:40:06.455 align:middle line:84%
is ultimately privatization
of public institutions.

00:40:06.455 --> 00:40:07.080 align:middle line:90%
>>PERKINS: Yes.

00:40:07.080 --> 00:40:09.650 align:middle line:84%
You know I've been spending
a lot of time recently--

00:40:09.650 --> 00:40:11.450 align:middle line:84%
and I spent a lot
of Latin America--

00:40:11.450 --> 00:40:13.440 align:middle line:84%
but I was also fairly
recently in Iceland

00:40:13.440 --> 00:40:17.270 align:middle line:84%
and I just came back from the
United Kingdom and Ireland

00:40:17.270 --> 00:40:19.180 align:middle line:90%
and lecturing in these places.

00:40:19.180 --> 00:40:23.970 align:middle line:84%
And what's been going
on throughout Europe,

00:40:23.970 --> 00:40:27.720 align:middle line:84%
and I would include Iceland
as part of that category,

00:40:27.720 --> 00:40:31.100 align:middle line:90%
is a big hit by economic hitmen.

00:40:31.100 --> 00:40:36.840 align:middle line:84%
And there's been this intent of
putting people deep into debt,

00:40:36.840 --> 00:40:38.750 align:middle line:84%
whether it's national
debt or personal debt,

00:40:38.750 --> 00:40:41.470 align:middle line:84%
private debt, as
a way of getting

00:40:41.470 --> 00:40:43.560 align:middle line:90%
more and more control over them.

00:40:43.560 --> 00:40:46.110 align:middle line:84%
And there's many
different iterations.

00:40:46.110 --> 00:40:47.700 align:middle line:84%
So what happened
in Iceland is quite

00:40:47.700 --> 00:40:49.408 align:middle line:84%
different from what's
happening in Greece

00:40:49.408 --> 00:40:51.960 align:middle line:84%
and what's happening in
Spain, which Spain now

00:40:51.960 --> 00:40:54.260 align:middle line:90%
is in the deep depression.

00:40:54.260 --> 00:40:54.760 align:middle line:90%
More than--

00:40:54.760 --> 00:40:55.800 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: What is
it, 50% unemployment?

00:40:55.800 --> 00:40:58.010 align:middle line:84%
>>PERKINS: -50% of its
young people are unemployed.

00:40:58.010 --> 00:41:00.920 align:middle line:84%
And what's happening in
Ireland is different.

00:41:00.920 --> 00:41:08.506 align:middle line:84%
But in all these cases, you
can see that the solution today

00:41:08.506 --> 00:41:12.510 align:middle line:84%
advocated by the big
banks and by governments

00:41:12.510 --> 00:41:15.150 align:middle line:84%
primarily, because they're
controlled by the big banks

00:41:15.150 --> 00:41:17.030 align:middle line:84%
or they're in
collusion with them--

00:41:17.030 --> 00:41:19.140 align:middle line:90%
is austerity for the people.

00:41:19.140 --> 00:41:20.820 align:middle line:90%
Don't tax the wealthy.

00:41:20.820 --> 00:41:22.960 align:middle line:84%
Don't do anything to hurt
the banks or the wealthy,

00:41:22.960 --> 00:41:25.900 align:middle line:84%
but force the people into
deeper and deeper austerity.

00:41:25.900 --> 00:41:27.230 align:middle line:90%
That is not the answer.

00:41:27.230 --> 00:41:27.730 align:middle line:90%
We know.

00:41:27.730 --> 00:41:28.710 align:middle line:90%
I'm an economist.

00:41:28.710 --> 00:41:32.590 align:middle line:84%
Any self-respecting economist
who has really studied

00:41:32.590 --> 00:41:35.411 align:middle line:84%
the Great Depression and other
depressions knows that what

00:41:35.411 --> 00:41:36.160 align:middle line:90%
you've got to do--

00:41:36.160 --> 00:41:37.130 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: You don't
punish the people.

00:41:37.130 --> 00:41:38.150 align:middle line:84%
>>PERKINS: You don't
punish the people.

00:41:38.150 --> 00:41:40.380 align:middle line:84%
And you do invest money in
things that employ people.

00:41:40.380 --> 00:41:42.440 align:middle line:90%
What we need is employment.

00:41:42.440 --> 00:41:43.450 align:middle line:90%
That is the big one.

00:41:43.450 --> 00:41:47.320 align:middle line:84%
It doesn't matter that the
GNP or GDP is going up,

00:41:47.320 --> 00:41:49.600 align:middle line:84%
that a few corporations
and a few individuals,

00:41:49.600 --> 00:41:54.200 align:middle line:84%
this 0.000035% of the
population, is doing better.

00:41:54.200 --> 00:41:57.670 align:middle line:84%
That may make the statistics
go up, but what we really need

00:41:57.670 --> 00:42:01.030 align:middle line:84%
is to get employment,
to get people to work,

00:42:01.030 --> 00:42:03.640 align:middle line:84%
to get people to be able to
pay off these incredible debts

00:42:03.640 --> 00:42:06.840 align:middle line:84%
that they have on their credit
cards and on their homes.

00:42:06.840 --> 00:42:08.840 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: So what's this
double-edged sword then

00:42:08.840 --> 00:42:11.580 align:middle line:84%
where you're talking about going
into Greece, or any country

00:42:11.580 --> 00:42:15.550 align:middle line:84%
really, and then privatizing
public sector types

00:42:15.550 --> 00:42:17.810 align:middle line:90%
of institutional jobs and such.

00:42:17.810 --> 00:42:19.330 align:middle line:90%
On one hand, need jobs.

00:42:19.330 --> 00:42:22.060 align:middle line:84%
On the other, it wouldn't
be the government

00:42:22.060 --> 00:42:23.740 align:middle line:84%
that would be providing
that any longer.

00:42:23.740 --> 00:42:27.140 align:middle line:84%
It would be some of these
preferred private corporations.

00:42:27.140 --> 00:42:29.346 align:middle line:84%
>>PERKINS: It's called
asset stripping,

00:42:29.346 --> 00:42:31.370 align:middle line:84%
and it's part of
empire building.

00:42:31.370 --> 00:42:33.500 align:middle line:90%
It's as old as empire.

00:42:33.500 --> 00:42:37.500 align:middle line:84%
And it's what part of my job was
when I was an economic hitman,

00:42:37.500 --> 00:42:41.680 align:middle line:84%
was to put these
countries deep into debt,

00:42:41.680 --> 00:42:43.820 align:middle line:84%
and then they
couldn't pay the debt.

00:42:43.820 --> 00:42:45.870 align:middle line:84%
So then we go back
in-- usually it

00:42:45.870 --> 00:42:47.870 align:middle line:84%
was the World Bank and
its sisters that put them

00:42:47.870 --> 00:42:50.590 align:middle line:84%
into the debt, along with
me, the economic hitman.

00:42:50.590 --> 00:42:54.860 align:middle line:84%
Then the IMF goes in to help
them restructure the debt.

00:42:54.860 --> 00:42:57.480 align:middle line:84%
What the IMF does
is demand that they

00:42:57.480 --> 00:43:00.512 align:middle line:84%
have certain forms of
government, A, that we like.

00:43:00.512 --> 00:43:02.220 align:middle line:84%
They don't have to be
democratic, as long

00:43:02.220 --> 00:43:04.390 align:middle line:84%
as they are supporting
our corporations.

00:43:04.390 --> 00:43:07.690 align:middle line:84%
And that they sell what
we'd consider public assets,

00:43:07.690 --> 00:43:11.130 align:middle line:84%
like electric companies and
water and sewage companies,

00:43:11.130 --> 00:43:13.990 align:middle line:84%
and maybe their prisons and
their schools and their ports

00:43:13.990 --> 00:43:15.800 align:middle line:84%
and their airports
and their highways,

00:43:15.800 --> 00:43:18.770 align:middle line:84%
sell them to private
corporations.

00:43:18.770 --> 00:43:20.720 align:middle line:84%
So again, it goes
back to this theory

00:43:20.720 --> 00:43:22.770 align:middle line:84%
that the only
responsibility of business

00:43:22.770 --> 00:43:25.210 align:middle line:84%
is to maximize profits,
and businesses shouldn't

00:43:25.210 --> 00:43:28.040 align:middle line:84%
be regulated, and everything
should be privatized.

00:43:28.040 --> 00:43:31.080 align:middle line:84%
Get government out, let the
big corporations control

00:43:31.080 --> 00:43:32.100 align:middle line:90%
the governments.

00:43:32.100 --> 00:43:33.130 align:middle line:90%
They control the assets.

00:43:33.130 --> 00:43:35.490 align:middle line:90%
And in fact, it's happened.

00:43:35.490 --> 00:43:37.560 align:middle line:84%
Even before they
control the assets,

00:43:37.560 --> 00:43:39.400 align:middle line:84%
already the big
corporations control

00:43:39.400 --> 00:43:40.970 align:middle line:84%
most of the world's
major governments

00:43:40.970 --> 00:43:42.240 align:middle line:90%
in one way or another.

00:43:42.240 --> 00:43:44.680 align:middle line:84%
And they control the
mainstream press.

00:43:44.680 --> 00:43:47.260 align:middle line:84%
And so this asset
stripping is just

00:43:47.260 --> 00:43:48.857 align:middle line:90%
another step in that direction.

00:43:48.857 --> 00:43:51.440 align:middle line:84%
It's putting everything in the
hands of the big corporations--

00:43:51.440 --> 00:43:55.010 align:middle line:84%
of what I call the
corporatocracy, the few,

00:43:55.010 --> 00:43:59.260 align:middle line:84%
primarily men, few women around
the world who run our biggest

00:43:59.260 --> 00:44:00.544 align:middle line:90%
multinational corporations.

00:44:00.544 --> 00:44:02.210 align:middle line:84%
They're the ones who
are taking control.

00:44:02.210 --> 00:44:05.390 align:middle line:84%
They're the modern
equivalent of the emperor.

00:44:05.390 --> 00:44:07.320 align:middle line:90%
And I think this is the hope.

00:44:07.320 --> 00:44:09.280 align:middle line:84%
That every one of us
needs to recognize

00:44:09.280 --> 00:44:12.220 align:middle line:84%
that we, as individuals,
have tremendous power,

00:44:12.220 --> 00:44:14.180 align:middle line:90%
each individual, we all have it.

00:44:14.180 --> 00:44:16.510 align:middle line:90%
And each of us has passions.

00:44:16.510 --> 00:44:18.780 align:middle line:90%
And we have talents.

00:44:18.780 --> 00:44:21.541 align:middle line:84%
So I have a passion for
writing, and hopefully,

00:44:21.541 --> 00:44:22.290 align:middle line:90%
some talent at it.

00:44:22.290 --> 00:44:25.680 align:middle line:84%
You have a passion and talent
for producing documentaries

00:44:25.680 --> 00:44:26.730 align:middle line:90%
and films.

00:44:26.730 --> 00:44:28.950 align:middle line:84%
But everybody has
passion and talent.

00:44:28.950 --> 00:44:32.270 align:middle line:84%
And if we all channel those
passions and those talents

00:44:32.270 --> 00:44:34.270 align:middle line:84%
toward creating a
sustainable, just,

00:44:34.270 --> 00:44:36.750 align:middle line:84%
peaceful world that's
thriving for all beings--

00:44:36.750 --> 00:44:37.680 align:middle line:90%
we will get there.

00:44:37.680 --> 00:44:40.070 align:middle line:84%
I think this needs to
be the mantra today.

00:44:40.070 --> 00:44:41.600 align:middle line:84%
And we need to
recognize that we've

00:44:41.600 --> 00:44:44.550 align:middle line:84%
got to force the corporations--
that the corporations are

00:44:44.550 --> 00:44:45.560 align:middle line:90%
very, very vulnerable.

00:44:45.560 --> 00:44:48.570 align:middle line:84%
They're running the world,
and we run them ultimately.

00:44:48.570 --> 00:44:49.300 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Right.

00:44:49.300 --> 00:44:51.430 align:middle line:84%
>>PERKINS: The marketplace
is a democracy,

00:44:51.430 --> 00:44:52.940 align:middle line:90%
if we choose to make it that.

00:44:52.940 --> 00:44:54.860 align:middle line:84%
And we've shown this
time and time again.

00:44:54.860 --> 00:44:58.200 align:middle line:84%
When I was in college, there
was apartheid in South Africa

00:44:58.200 --> 00:45:00.240 align:middle line:84%
and we boycotted
corporations that

00:45:00.240 --> 00:45:02.140 align:middle line:90%
supported it and it changed.

00:45:02.140 --> 00:45:05.470 align:middle line:84%
And now I think we have
to take this up a notch

00:45:05.470 --> 00:45:07.409 align:middle line:84%
and convince the
corporations we're only

00:45:07.409 --> 00:45:09.700 align:middle line:84%
going to buy from those
corporations that are committed

00:45:09.700 --> 00:45:12.380 align:middle line:84%
to making a decent rate of
return on their capital.

00:45:12.380 --> 00:45:12.940 align:middle line:90%
That's OK.

00:45:12.940 --> 00:45:14.944 align:middle line:84%
But not maximizing
profits regardless

00:45:14.944 --> 00:45:16.360 align:middle line:84%
of social and
environmental cause.

00:45:16.360 --> 00:45:18.750 align:middle line:84%
They've got to be
committed to being socially

00:45:18.750 --> 00:45:22.110 align:middle line:84%
and environmentally
responsible, to creating a world

00:45:22.110 --> 00:45:25.590 align:middle line:84%
that my grandson, who is 5 years
old, will want to grow up in.

00:45:25.590 --> 00:45:27.880 align:middle line:84%
And to recognize
that that world has

00:45:27.880 --> 00:45:30.420 align:middle line:84%
to include every
child on the planet.

00:45:30.420 --> 00:45:31.580 align:middle line:90%
And this is new in history.

00:45:31.580 --> 00:45:33.830 align:middle line:84%
We used to only have to worry
about the United States.

00:45:33.830 --> 00:45:35.230 align:middle line:84%
That was certainly
true in World War II.

00:45:35.230 --> 00:45:36.688 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: It is a
global community.

00:45:36.688 --> 00:45:39.475 align:middle line:84%
>>PERKINS: Today, we've got
to recognize that my grandson

00:45:39.475 --> 00:45:43.210 align:middle line:84%
in the United States cannot
inherit a sustainable, just,

00:45:43.210 --> 00:45:45.980 align:middle line:84%
peaceful, thriving world
unless every child growing up

00:45:45.980 --> 00:45:50.310 align:middle line:84%
in Bolivia, Botswana,
Indonesia, Palestine,

00:45:50.310 --> 00:45:53.390 align:middle line:84%
and Israel also inherits
that same world.

00:45:53.390 --> 00:45:54.520 align:middle line:90%
This is new.

00:45:54.520 --> 00:45:56.606 align:middle line:84%
We've discovered--
and we're all talking

00:45:56.606 --> 00:45:57.980 align:middle line:84%
to each other for
the first time,

00:45:57.980 --> 00:45:59.650 align:middle line:84%
we're communicating
across the planet

00:45:59.650 --> 00:46:01.480 align:middle line:84%
through all these
technologies, and we've

00:46:01.480 --> 00:46:05.730 align:middle line:84%
discovered that we're living
on a very, very fragile space

00:46:05.730 --> 00:46:06.880 align:middle line:90%
station.

00:46:06.880 --> 00:46:10.900 align:middle line:84%
But unlike the space station
that our astronauts built,

00:46:10.900 --> 00:46:13.520 align:middle line:84%
this one doesn't
have any shuttles.

00:46:13.520 --> 00:46:14.947 align:middle line:90%
You can't get off.

00:46:14.947 --> 00:46:16.260 align:middle line:90%
I can't get off.

00:46:16.260 --> 00:46:21.360 align:middle line:84%
And debt is the modern
chains of slavery.

00:46:21.360 --> 00:46:22.470 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Absolutely.

00:46:22.470 --> 00:46:25.110 align:middle line:84%
Let's get to Latin Americans
and what happened there,

00:46:25.110 --> 00:46:26.780 align:middle line:84%
some recent scandals
that occurred

00:46:26.780 --> 00:46:28.209 align:middle line:90%
and the extension of that.

00:46:28.209 --> 00:46:29.750 align:middle line:84%
>>PERKINS: Well,
first of all, I want

00:46:29.750 --> 00:46:32.250 align:middle line:84%
to say that in
the last 10 years,

00:46:32.250 --> 00:46:37.280 align:middle line:84%
10 countries in Latin America
representing more than 80%

00:46:37.280 --> 00:46:40.170 align:middle line:84%
of the population
of South America

00:46:40.170 --> 00:46:42.340 align:middle line:84%
have voted in in
democratic elections,

00:46:42.340 --> 00:46:44.870 align:middle line:84%
presidents that have stood
up to the corporatocracy.

00:46:44.870 --> 00:46:46.620 align:middle line:84%
There have been varying
different degrees.

00:46:46.620 --> 00:46:47.180 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: It's been amazing.

00:46:47.180 --> 00:46:47.846 align:middle line:90%
>>PERKINS: Yeah.

00:46:47.846 --> 00:46:51.420 align:middle line:84%
It's been different in
Bolivia from Ecuador or Chile

00:46:51.420 --> 00:46:53.190 align:middle line:84%
or Argentina, they're
all different.

00:46:53.190 --> 00:46:54.940 align:middle line:84%
But every one of
these 10 countries

00:46:54.940 --> 00:46:58.130 align:middle line:84%
during most of my lifetime
was run by brutal dictators,

00:46:58.130 --> 00:47:01.060 align:middle line:84%
primarily put into power by the
CIA and kept there by the CIA.

00:47:01.060 --> 00:47:02.390 align:middle line:90%
And this is all changed.

00:47:02.390 --> 00:47:05.540 align:middle line:84%
It actually changed
after 2002, after Chavez

00:47:05.540 --> 00:47:07.329 align:middle line:84%
showed that he could
stand up to the CIA.

00:47:07.329 --> 00:47:08.870 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: And he
wasn't assassinated.

00:47:08.870 --> 00:47:09.180 align:middle line:90%
>>PERKINS: No.

00:47:09.180 --> 00:47:09.680 align:middle line:90%
Well, no.

00:47:09.680 --> 00:47:11.610 align:middle line:90%
We backed down.

00:47:11.610 --> 00:47:13.990 align:middle line:84%
Bush and the CIA were
shown as paper tigers.

00:47:13.990 --> 00:47:18.110 align:middle line:84%
And you can think whatever
you want about Chavez,

00:47:18.110 --> 00:47:19.446 align:middle line:90%
he's eccentric to say the least.

00:47:19.446 --> 00:47:20.820 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: He's a
big personality.

00:47:20.820 --> 00:47:21.880 align:middle line:84%
>>PERKINS: But the
fact of the matter

00:47:21.880 --> 00:47:23.505 align:middle line:84%
is he changed history
in Latin America.

00:47:23.505 --> 00:47:24.530 align:middle line:90%
So big things happened.

00:47:24.530 --> 00:47:26.654 align:middle line:84%
There's been a real
revolution, a quiet revolution.

00:47:26.654 --> 00:47:29.060 align:middle line:84%
We don't talk about it
in the United States.

00:47:29.060 --> 00:47:30.680 align:middle line:84%
It doesn't make the
press even hardly.

00:47:30.680 --> 00:47:32.410 align:middle line:90%
But it's been big.

00:47:32.410 --> 00:47:34.565 align:middle line:84%
And one example of how
it doesn't make the press

00:47:34.565 --> 00:47:38.020 align:middle line:84%
is that the recent summit that
was held in Cartagena, Colombia

00:47:38.020 --> 00:47:43.780 align:middle line:84%
that Obama was at, the majority
of the presidents of Latin

00:47:43.780 --> 00:47:46.350 align:middle line:84%
America really
strongly protested

00:47:46.350 --> 00:47:48.941 align:middle line:84%
US policies toward drug
trafficking and the fact

00:47:48.941 --> 00:47:50.565 align:middle line:84%
that they said, you've
got to get drugs

00:47:50.565 --> 00:47:52.320 align:middle line:90%
under control in your country.

00:47:52.320 --> 00:47:54.560 align:middle line:84%
It's not about sending
your military down here

00:47:54.560 --> 00:47:56.320 align:middle line:84%
or your CIA to Columbia, or
Mexico or other countries.

00:47:56.320 --> 00:47:57.630 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: We're the consumers.

00:47:57.630 --> 00:47:58.963 align:middle line:90%
>>PERKINS: You're the consumers.

00:47:58.963 --> 00:48:03.370 align:middle line:84%
Mr. President, Mr. Obama
take this seriously.

00:48:03.370 --> 00:48:05.470 align:middle line:84%
And several other
issues like this

00:48:05.470 --> 00:48:08.030 align:middle line:84%
never made the news
in the United States.

00:48:08.030 --> 00:48:13.290 align:middle line:84%
And instead, we focused on a
dozen Secret Security agents

00:48:13.290 --> 00:48:16.210 align:middle line:84%
who had prostitutes in their
hotel room, which incidentally

00:48:16.210 --> 00:48:17.465 align:middle line:90%
is not illegal in Colombia.

00:48:17.465 --> 00:48:20.420 align:middle line:84%
It may be against the
Secret Service policy,

00:48:20.420 --> 00:48:22.830 align:middle line:84%
but what concerned
me is I couldn't

00:48:22.830 --> 00:48:25.320 align:middle line:84%
get any news about
what was going

00:48:25.320 --> 00:48:27.110 align:middle line:84%
on in that summit
in the US press.

00:48:27.110 --> 00:48:31.660 align:middle line:84%
Just minimal amounts except
about the prostitution

00:48:31.660 --> 00:48:33.720 align:middle line:90%
scandal with the Secret Service.

00:48:33.720 --> 00:48:35.760 align:middle line:84%
To get the real news,
I had to go online.

00:48:35.760 --> 00:48:37.100 align:middle line:90%
Fortunately, I read Spanish.

00:48:37.100 --> 00:48:40.166 align:middle line:84%
I could get the real news from
Latin American publications.

00:48:40.166 --> 00:48:41.540 align:middle line:84%
But the American
people are being

00:48:41.540 --> 00:48:44.104 align:middle line:84%
kept in the dark
in so many ways.

00:48:44.104 --> 00:48:45.520 align:middle line:84%
And one of the big
things is we're

00:48:45.520 --> 00:48:47.436 align:middle line:84%
kept in the dark about
the amazing things that

00:48:47.436 --> 00:48:49.590 align:middle line:84%
have been going on
in Latin America.

00:48:49.590 --> 00:48:52.450 align:middle line:84%
And now the fact that we are
overthrowing governments,

00:48:52.450 --> 00:48:57.690 align:middle line:84%
like Zelaya and attempt
at Correa in Ecuador--

00:48:57.690 --> 00:49:02.120 align:middle line:84%
and because these countries have
elected these presidents now,

00:49:02.120 --> 00:49:04.100 align:middle line:84%
the economic hitmen
are going in.

00:49:04.100 --> 00:49:06.130 align:middle line:84%
They're playing the game
that I used to play.

00:49:06.130 --> 00:49:09.320 align:middle line:84%
And you know, just a few months
ago I spoke at a conference

00:49:09.320 --> 00:49:10.330 align:middle line:90%
in Istanbul.

00:49:10.330 --> 00:49:14.980 align:middle line:84%
4,000 leaders of the
communications industry,

00:49:14.980 --> 00:49:18.110 align:middle line:84%
CFOs and CEOs of big
communications companies, and I

00:49:18.110 --> 00:49:20.078 align:middle line:90%
was the keynote opening speaker.

00:49:20.078 --> 00:49:21.536 align:middle line:84%
And what I said to
these people is,

00:49:21.536 --> 00:49:23.680 align:middle line:84%
you know, we've created
a world-- now you've

00:49:23.680 --> 00:49:25.520 align:middle line:84%
created a world
where everybody's

00:49:25.520 --> 00:49:28.140 align:middle line:84%
talking to everybody else
through the internet,

00:49:28.140 --> 00:49:32.670 align:middle line:84%
through Skyping,
through cell phones.

00:49:32.670 --> 00:49:34.577 align:middle line:84%
But you now have
to ask yourselves,

00:49:34.577 --> 00:49:36.660 align:middle line:84%
what do you want these
people to be communicating?

00:49:36.660 --> 00:49:39.076 align:middle line:84%
What are you going to encourage
them to communicate about?

00:49:39.076 --> 00:49:41.040 align:middle line:84%
Do you want them to
continue to discuss the sex

00:49:41.040 --> 00:49:43.690 align:middle line:84%
lives of Hollywood
stars and politicians?

00:49:43.690 --> 00:49:45.800 align:middle line:84%
The latest fashions
in Paris and New York?

00:49:45.800 --> 00:49:46.360 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Who is in rehab?

00:49:46.360 --> 00:49:47.485 align:middle line:90%
>>PERKINS: Who is in rehab?

00:49:47.485 --> 00:49:51.350 align:middle line:84%
And who's winning the World
Cup and so on and so forth.

00:49:51.350 --> 00:49:52.680 align:middle line:90%
Maybe a little bit.

00:49:52.680 --> 00:49:56.010 align:middle line:84%
But let's focus on
what's really important.

00:49:56.010 --> 00:49:57.977 align:middle line:84%
And people are
hungering for this.

00:49:57.977 --> 00:49:58.560 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Yes.

00:49:58.560 --> 00:50:01.110 align:middle line:84%
It's not like there's a
shortage of good information.

00:50:01.110 --> 00:50:04.430 align:middle line:84%
It's just that en mass, we
need to start valuing it.

00:50:04.430 --> 00:50:06.860 align:middle line:84%
And also, talk about
the corporatocracy

00:50:06.860 --> 00:50:08.770 align:middle line:90%
and its power or not.

00:50:08.770 --> 00:50:11.264 align:middle line:84%
As you said earlier, the power
is actually in our hands,

00:50:11.264 --> 00:50:12.930 align:middle line:84%
all you have to do
is turn off the media

00:50:12.930 --> 00:50:14.232 align:middle line:90%
and now you have panic.

00:50:14.232 --> 00:50:16.190 align:middle line:84%
There are a lot of
advertising dollars flowing,

00:50:16.190 --> 00:50:18.020 align:middle line:84%
a lot of impressions
that are trying

00:50:18.020 --> 00:50:21.430 align:middle line:84%
to be laid through that
media to sell those products,

00:50:21.430 --> 00:50:23.870 align:middle line:84%
so that they can keep these
ridiculous policies going

00:50:23.870 --> 00:50:24.850 align:middle line:90%
in other countries.

00:50:24.850 --> 00:50:26.420 align:middle line:84%
It's a really
interesting circle.

00:50:26.420 --> 00:50:27.419 align:middle line:90%
>>PERKINS: Well, it is.

00:50:27.419 --> 00:50:29.460 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: It's really all
in our hands, isn't it?

00:50:29.460 --> 00:50:30.430 align:middle line:90%
>>PERKINS: Yes, it is.

00:50:30.430 --> 00:50:32.905 align:middle line:84%
We do have control if
we just recognize that.

00:50:32.905 --> 00:50:35.280 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: And the Dalai Lama,
you sat next-- I love this.

00:50:35.280 --> 00:50:38.410 align:middle line:84%
I asked you this last time-- but
the Dalai Lama was next to you

00:50:38.410 --> 00:50:40.080 align:middle line:84%
on the airplane
one time and he had

00:50:40.080 --> 00:50:43.120 align:middle line:84%
read "Confessions of an
Economic Hit Man," hadn't he?

00:50:43.120 --> 00:50:45.370 align:middle line:84%
>>PERKINS: He had read-- it
was before it was came out

00:50:45.370 --> 00:50:46.440 align:middle line:90%
actually.

00:50:46.440 --> 00:50:47.730 align:middle line:90%
He'd read "Shape Shifting."

00:50:47.730 --> 00:50:49.170 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: "Shape Shifting," OK.

00:50:49.170 --> 00:50:52.542 align:middle line:10%
And so you were talking
with him back and forth,

00:50:52.542 --> 00:50:54.500 align:middle line:10%
and wasn't he telling
you something, I thought,

00:50:54.500 --> 00:50:57.860 align:middle line:10%
profound about
meditation is great but.

00:50:57.860 --> 00:50:59.404 align:middle line:84%
>>PERKINS: Yeah,
so the Dalai Lama

00:50:59.404 --> 00:51:01.320 align:middle line:84%
invited me to sit next
to him on the airplane.

00:51:01.320 --> 00:51:04.510 align:middle line:84%
And then he invited my whole
group--I was leading a group

00:51:04.510 --> 00:51:07.750 align:middle line:84%
of about 30 people-- to
his house in Dharamsala

00:51:07.750 --> 00:51:09.190 align:middle line:84%
for a meeting in
his living room.

00:51:09.190 --> 00:51:12.400 align:middle line:84%
And at that talk
he said, "You know,

00:51:12.400 --> 00:51:15.380 align:middle line:84%
it's good to meditate
and pray for peace,

00:51:15.380 --> 00:51:19.770 align:middle line:84%
but if that's all you do,
forget it, because," he said,

00:51:19.770 --> 00:51:21.500 align:middle line:90%
"we have to take action, too."

00:51:21.500 --> 00:51:24.380 align:middle line:84%
And in fact, he went on
to say that if all you do

00:51:24.380 --> 00:51:26.630 align:middle line:84%
is pray for peace and
meditate for peace and figure

00:51:26.630 --> 00:51:28.690 align:middle line:84%
you've done your
job and walk away,

00:51:28.690 --> 00:51:29.960 align:middle line:90%
then it's counterproductive.

00:51:29.960 --> 00:51:32.680 align:middle line:84%
Because we've really all got
to go out and take action

00:51:32.680 --> 00:51:34.620 align:middle line:90%
every single day.

00:51:34.620 --> 00:51:37.410 align:middle line:84%
And I think the Dalai Lama is
such a great example of that.

00:51:37.410 --> 00:51:39.470 align:middle line:84%
Here's one of the world's
great spiritual leaders

00:51:39.470 --> 00:51:41.600 align:middle line:84%
who meditates for
hours every day,

00:51:41.600 --> 00:51:43.030 align:middle line:90%
but he's also always out there.

00:51:43.030 --> 00:51:45.977 align:middle line:84%
He's got hundreds of
best selling books out.

00:51:45.977 --> 00:51:47.435 align:middle line:84%
He seems to be
speaking everywhere.

00:51:47.435 --> 00:51:48.922 align:middle line:84%
I travel around
the world speaking

00:51:48.922 --> 00:51:50.838 align:middle line:84%
and the Dalai Lama is
always right ahead of me

00:51:50.838 --> 00:51:52.250 align:middle line:90%
or right behind me.

00:51:52.250 --> 00:51:53.014 align:middle line:90%
He's everywhere.

00:51:53.014 --> 00:51:55.180 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: And he's had to
deal with political strife

00:51:55.180 --> 00:51:59.550 align:middle line:84%
and manipulation in his
own country and his people.

00:51:59.550 --> 00:52:02.580 align:middle line:84%
So it's not as though he's
not familiar with this.

00:52:02.580 --> 00:52:05.200 align:middle line:84%
He understands what happens
when a government chooses

00:52:05.200 --> 00:52:08.880 align:middle line:84%
to lay an impression
or unseat indigenous

00:52:08.880 --> 00:52:10.062 align:middle line:90%
people and their ways.

00:52:10.062 --> 00:52:12.270 align:middle line:84%
>>PERKINS: The Dalai Lama's
a great example that way.

00:52:12.270 --> 00:52:14.680 align:middle line:84%
And Mother Teresa
was another one.

00:52:14.680 --> 00:52:15.630 align:middle line:90%
And there's so many.

00:52:15.630 --> 00:52:18.449 align:middle line:84%
There's a lot of people
doing amazing, amazing things

00:52:18.449 --> 00:52:18.990 align:middle line:90%
in the world.

00:52:18.990 --> 00:52:22.420 align:middle line:84%
I think what we each have to
recognize is that each of us

00:52:22.420 --> 00:52:24.450 align:middle line:90%
has that ability.

00:52:24.450 --> 00:52:28.335 align:middle line:84%
Every one of us has the ability
to do what Rosa Parks did

00:52:28.335 --> 00:52:29.820 align:middle line:90%
and walk to the front of a bus.

00:52:29.820 --> 00:52:33.270 align:middle line:84%
It may take courage, but
she changed the world

00:52:33.270 --> 00:52:35.260 align:middle line:84%
by walking to the
front of a bus.

00:52:35.260 --> 00:52:38.370 align:middle line:84%
Or Rachel Carson sat down
one day at a little desk

00:52:38.370 --> 00:52:41.980 align:middle line:84%
in Pennsylvania and started
scribbling out with a pencil

00:52:41.980 --> 00:52:44.420 align:middle line:90%
a book called "Silent Spring."

00:52:44.420 --> 00:52:46.560 align:middle line:84%
She had no idea it
would ever be published.

00:52:46.560 --> 00:52:48.604 align:middle line:84%
Much less that it would start
a whole environmental movement

00:52:48.604 --> 00:52:49.312 align:middle line:90%
around the world.

00:52:49.312 --> 00:52:53.000 align:middle line:84%
It really was the
driving force behind what

00:52:53.000 --> 00:52:54.850 align:middle line:84%
today is the
environmental movement.

00:52:54.850 --> 00:52:56.890 align:middle line:84%
She just sat down at a
desk and started writing.

00:52:56.890 --> 00:53:02.010 align:middle line:84%
We all have the power to do
whatever it is we do best,

00:53:02.010 --> 00:53:04.400 align:middle line:84%
and to recognize that
it can change the world.

00:53:04.400 --> 00:53:06.280 align:middle line:90%
Each one of us has that ability.

00:53:06.280 --> 00:53:09.340 align:middle line:84%
And when we all come together
and commit to doing that,

00:53:09.340 --> 00:53:10.640 align:middle line:90%
it will happen.

00:53:10.640 --> 00:53:11.804 align:middle line:90%
I'm very hopeful.

00:53:11.804 --> 00:53:12.970 align:middle line:90%
I know it's going to happen.

00:53:12.970 --> 00:53:14.500 align:middle line:84%
I know we're going
to pull through this

00:53:14.500 --> 00:53:15.510 align:middle line:90%
and we're going to do this.

00:53:15.510 --> 00:53:16.330 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: I agree with you.

00:53:16.330 --> 00:53:16.955 align:middle line:90%
I think we are.

00:53:16.955 --> 00:53:19.330 align:middle line:84%
And it's really going to
rest on the next generation.

00:53:19.330 --> 00:53:21.780 align:middle line:84%
And as we wrap up
our conversation,

00:53:21.780 --> 00:53:24.600 align:middle line:84%
any final comment about--
you've mentioned your grandson

00:53:24.600 --> 00:53:27.220 align:middle line:84%
a couple of times now,
who is now five years old,

00:53:27.220 --> 00:53:32.540 align:middle line:84%
any thoughts on how we
inspire the next generation

00:53:32.540 --> 00:53:34.710 align:middle line:84%
or what our
responsibility to them

00:53:34.710 --> 00:53:38.720 align:middle line:84%
is in releasing these
charades, these illusions?

00:53:38.720 --> 00:53:42.190 align:middle line:84%
>>PERKINS: I think what we
need to tell this upcoming

00:53:42.190 --> 00:53:45.140 align:middle line:84%
generation, and I do every
chance I get in speaking out

00:53:45.140 --> 00:53:48.560 align:middle line:84%
and so forth and with young
kids too, very young kids, is

00:53:48.560 --> 00:53:51.110 align:middle line:84%
